body:
@DaanHoogland There are many different solutions in place, some are bash/python scripts that do `>/var/log/cloud.log` etc, some use `nohup` to keep running and others are daemons that also log into the same file. There is no easy way to make logrotate restart those without some refactoring.

Also, close to release I didn't want to refactor the whole thing, as we'll have regression issues from that if we do it too quickly. 

This seems a safe fix for now, we should refactor it in the next release. Using syslog could be a simple solution, as that handles many of these scenarios already.
